Japanese Sold Net 468.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-09-14T23:52:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/japanese-sold-net-468-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended Sept. 9 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 468.4 billion yen ($6.1 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 64.7 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 23 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 426.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 762.1 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 588.9 billion yen in stocks, and bought 553.1 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 726.3
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  